p: According to the analysis of the medical records, the total number of suspected cases for arboviruses in 2015 was 969 (4,296/100,000 inhabitants), and of these 146 (15.1%) were classified as caused by ZIKV, and in 2016, there were 2012 suspected cases (8,866/100,000 inhabitants) of which 777 (38.6%) were classified as ZIKV.
